{{Nihongo|'''Kōki Ogawa'''|小川 航基|Ogawa Kōki|born 8 August 1997}} is a Japanese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Eredivisie]] club [[NEC Nijmegen]] and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].<ref>{{cite web |title=小川 航基：横浜ＦＣ：Ｊリーグ.jp |url=https://www.jleague.jp/player/1600008/#attack |website=Ｊリーグ.jp（日本プロサッカーリーグ） |access-date=4 December 2022 |language=ja}}</ref><ref>[https://data.j-league.or.jp/SFIX04/?player_id=19169 J.League Data Site]</ref>

==Club career==
Kōki Ogawa joined [[J1 League]] club [[Júbilo Iwata]] in 2016. On 6 April, he debuted in [[J.League Cup]] (v [[Ventforet Kofu]]).<ref>[https://data.j-league.or.jp/SFIX04/?player_id=19169 J.League Data Site]</ref><ref>[https://data.j-league.or.jp/SFMS02/?match_card_id=18911 Match report J.League Data Site]</ref>

Ogawa joined [[J2 League]] club, [[Mito HollyHock]] in 2019 on loan from [[Júbilo Iwata]].<ref>{{Cite press release|title=小川 航基選手 ジュビロ磐田より育成型期限付き移籍加入のお知らせ|url=https://www.mito-hollyhock.net/news/14862/|publisher=水戸ホーリーホック|date=14 July 2019|accessdate=14 July 2019}}</ref>

On 27 December 2021, Ogawa joined J2 club [[Yokohama FC]] for the 2022 season.<ref>{{cite press release|url=https://www.yokohamafc.com/2021/12/27/koki_ogawa/|title=小川 航基選手 ジュビロ磐田より完全移籍加入のお知らせ|publisher=横浜FC|date=27 December 2021|accessdate=27 December 2021}}</ref> At the end of the 2022 season, Yokohama FC gained promotion to the J1 League, with Ogawa contributing 26 goals during the season. As well as being the league's top scorer, he was named in the [[J.League Best XI|J2 League Best XI]] and won the overall J2 MVP award.<ref>{{cite web |title=最優秀選手賞（Ｊ２）は小川 航基選手（横浜ＦＣ）が初受賞！得点王（Ｊ２）とのＷ受賞に！！～優勝クラブのアルビレックス新潟からは6名がベストイレブン（Ｊ２）に選出～【Ｊ２リーグアウォーズ】：Ｊリーグ.jp |url=https://www.jleague.jp/news/article/23812/ |website=Ｊリーグ.jp（日本プロサッカーリーグ） |access-date=27 November 2022 |language=ja}}</ref>

In July 2023, Ogawa signed for [[Eredivisie]] club [[NEC Nijmegen]] on a season-long loan deal with the option to make the move permanent.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nec-nijmegen.nl/service-contact/vraag/n.e.c.-versterkt-zich-met-spits-koki-ogawa.htm|title=N.E.C. versterkt zich met spits Koki Ogawa|trans-title=NEC strengthens itself with striker Koki Ogawa|website=www.nec-nijmegen.nl|language=Dutch|date=4 July 2023|accessdate=4 July 2023}}</ref> On 21 March 2024, NEC exercised the purchase option and signed a three-year contract with Ogawa.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=NEC Nijmegen|url=https://www.nec-nijmegen.nl/nieuws/nieuws/n.e.c.-bindt-koki-ogawa-tot-2027-aan-zich.htm|title=N.E.C. bindt Koki Ogawa tot 2027 aan zich|trans-title=NEC signs Koki Ogawa until 2027|date=21 March 2024|access-date=15 July 2024|language=nl}}</ref>

==International career==
In May 2017, Ogawa was elected [[Japan national under-20 football team|Japan U-20 national team]] for [[2017 FIFA U-20 World Cup|2017 U-20 World Cup]]. At this tournament, he played first two matches. He scored a goal against [[South Africa national under-20 football team|South Africa]] in first match. However, because he was injured in second match against [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|Uruguay]], he could not play in later matches.

In December 2019, Kōki Ogawa was named in the senior squad to represent Japan in the [[2019 EAFF E-1 Football Championship|East Asia Cup]] finals. Ogawa scored his first hat-trick against [[Hong Kong national football team|Hong Kong]] in his senior debut.

On 18 November 2024, Ogawa scored two goals against China, representing Japan in the 2024 World Cup Asian Qualifier.<ref>{{Cite news |date=20 November 2024 |title=Football: Koki Ogawa brace sends Japan past China in World Cup qualifying |url=https://mainichi.jp/english/articles/20241120/p2g/00m/0sp/002000c |access-date=20 November 2024 |work=Mainichi Daily News |language=en}}</ref> Both goals were headers and demonstratred Ogawa's ability as a center forward for Japan.<ref>{{Cite web |last=NEWS |first=KYODO |title=Football: Ogawa brace sends Japan past China in World Cup qualifying |url=https://english.kyodonews.net/news/2024/11/d731e3ee51a2-football-ogawa-brace-sends-japan-past-china-in-world-cup-qualifying.html?phrase=Figure%20skating&words= |access-date=26 November 2024 |website=Kyodo News+}}</ref>

